@startuml
title Viaverse Analytics Event Ingestion — Activity Diagram
start
:Client/domain event;
:Capture event with schema version;
:Check consent and legal basis;
if (Allowed?) then (yes)
  :Sanitize payload\nremove PII/secrets;
  :Validate schema;
  if (Bad schema?) then (yes)
    :Send to DLQ;
    :Create quality alert;
  else (no)
    :Persist raw-safe event\nor stream to warehouse;
    :Update aggregates\nfunnel/cohort/kpi;
    :Refresh dashboard dataset;
    :Apply retention policy;
  endif
  :Emit quality/alert events;
else (no)
  :Drop or aggregate only;
endif
stop

note bottom
Every event has owner, schema version, retention class and sensitivity classification.
Unknown schemas go to DLQ, not silent production metrics.
end note
@enduml
